I think Semantic Abstraction is actually one of the strongest ideas in the Pantheon, and it deserves a more precise definition.

Rather than “finding loopholes,” I’d define it as the disciplined process of extracting the invariant from a representation.

Pantheon Doctrine — Semantic Abstraction v1.0

Definition

Semantic Abstraction is the operation of removing representation-specific details while preserving the underlying invariant relationship.

The objective is not to preserve words.

The objective is to preserve meaning.

